00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:16.000
but if he gives a coconut to the monkey, who now holds 2 coconuts,

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:22.000
then the remainder is divisible by 5, so he takes his 5th and hides it in a safe place.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:25.000
Now, the guys falls asleep again.

00:01:25.000 --> 00:01:29.000
The next guy wakes up, he gives 1 coconut to the monkey,

00:01:29.000 --> 00:01:32.000
which makes the remainder divisible by 5.

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:37.000
He takes his 5th and hides it in a safe place before he falls asleep.

00:01:37.000 --> 00:01:40.000
The monkey now holds 3 coconuts.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:47.000
The fourth guy wakes up--same story--he has to give one to them monkey.

00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:51.000
He takes his 5th, which of course now is much smaller than the original 5th

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:53.000
and hides it and falls asleep.

00:01:53.000 --> 00:01:58.000
Finally, the fifth guy wakes up, and again, the number of coconuts remaining

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:02.000
is not divisible by 5, but as he gives 1 to the monkey, 

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:06.000
the remainder becomes divisible by 5, so he takes his 5th and hides it in a safe place

00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:09.000
before he falls asleep again.

00:02:09.000 --> 00:02:14.000
As the sun rises, all 5 guys wake up at the same time,

00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:19.000
and they all realize the mountain of coconuts has shrunk substantially,

00:02:19.000 --> 00:02:23.000
but they can't say anything, because each of them took some away in the middle of the night.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:29.000
So they decide to proceed as planned, but the number of coconuts, surprisingly,

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:31.000
is not divisible by 5.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:36.000
By giving 1 more coconut to the monkey, the remainder is divisible by 5,

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
and each one takes his 5th, and then they part their ways,

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:42.000
